As customer reported:

{quote}
We are evaluating bamboo as possible jenkins replacement. However, our software director requires that our git repo's be tagged before and/or after each build. Is there a way for Bamboo to do this automatically or do you know of a plugin that can be used for tagging? I found this link, but we were hoping for a better solution: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/27371629/how-to-tag-a-git-repo-in-a-bamboo-build
{quote}

The document https://confluence.atlassian.com/bamboo/integrating-bamboo-with-hipchat-289276960.html in the paragraph: 
"Configure Bamboo plans to send notifications to your HipChat server" in item 1 suggest the following workaround:
{code}
Create a redirect in the /etc/hosts file on the server running Bamboo. The redirect should point api.hipchat.com to the fully qualified domain name (FQDN) for your organization's HipChat server.
{code}

Pointing a FQDN to api.hipchat.com in the hosts file doesn't work.
The correct would be:
{code}
Create a redirect in the /etc/hosts file on the server running Bamboo. The redirect should point  the ip address of your organization's HipChat server to api.hipchat.com

i.e.:
1.2.3.4   api.hipchat.com    
{code}

h2. Summary
Currently Bamboo has a refresh interval of 20 seconds for Ajax calls and does not provide a easy way to manage those events.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# open up Development panel in your web browser and go to Network section
# visit Build Dashboard - http://localhost:8085/allPlans.action
# visit Deployment Dashboard - http://localhost:8085/deploy/viewAllDeploymentProjects.action

h3. Results
By visiting the two URL from above, you should expected the following requests in a interval of 20s:
# http://localhost:8085/rest/api/latest/server?_=1444833915903 (_Build Dashboard_)
# http://localhost:8085/rest/api/latest/deploy/dashboard/?_=1444650761631 (_Deployment Dashboard_)

h3.Workaround
In order to change the interval, please:
{code:title=<bamboo-install>/atlassian-bamboo/scripts/bamboo.js}
/*
 * The following property is responsible for http://localhost:8085/allPlans.action interval/refresh
 * please, update '20' to a value (in seconds) you want to have the interval/refresh to happen
 */
BAMBOO.reloadDashboardTimeout = 20;
{code}
{code:title=<bamboo-install>/atlassian-bamboo/feature/deployment/project/project-list/project-list.js}
/*
 * The following property is responsible for http://localhost:8085/deploy/viewAllDeploymentProjects.action interval/refresh
 * please, update 'delayBeforeUpdate' to a value (in seconds) you want to have the interval/refresh to happen
 */
            this._timeout = setTimeout(
                _.bind(this.onUpdate, this),
                delayBeforeUpdate
            );
{code}

We are getting this error on Bamboo 5.7.2/Postgresql 9.1
{noformat}
2015-10-07 08:15:58,816 WARN [Timer-2] [ThreadPoolAsynchronousRunner] com.mchange.v2.async.ThreadPoolAsynchronousRunner$DeadlockDetector@5b197dc9 -- APPARENT DEADLOCK!!! Creating emergency threads for unassigned pending tasks!
{noformat}

{noformat}
2015-10-05 13:26:06,731 WARN [http-apr-80-exec-13] [JDBCExceptionReporter] SQL Error: 0, SQLState: 22025
2015-10-05 13:26:06,731 ERROR [http-apr-80-exec-13] [JDBCExceptionReporter] Prepared or callable statement has more than 2000 parameter markers.

{noformat}

This proves to be caused by a hardcoded limit in jTDS.
See e.g. https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-38790?focusedCommentId=616510&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-616510
